	<li id="comment-19577">
	<p>Great article, the more people that become aware of available privacy settings, the better.</p>
<p>The big one I would add to your list is blocking what applications your friends use can see &#8211; by default, much of what your friends can see about you can be seen by any application that they authorize (not which ones *you* authorize).  </p>
