	<li id="comment-19559">
	<p>My interpretation of this post can be summarized as, &#8220;Facebook privacy settings are too confusing for Facebook&#8217;s users.&#8221; This post would not exist if Facebook UX and docs were clear. It&#8217;s a shame, but if it were easy for users to control the use of their PII then Facebook would suffer. Facebook, quite simply, is incentivized to make their privacy settings confusing.</p>
<p>I emailed Facebook privacy support to explain that I don&#8217;t think reasonable people would think that &#8220;Use this to control who can see the full list of your friends on Facebook&#8221; means &#8220;(same) except for search results which ignore this setting.&#8221; Their response was to tell me that they looked at my privacy settings, and people could not see me in search results. I replied that they completely missed the point and that unless they had escalated the issue to their manager, I was shocked that they had read access rights to my settings. I no longer tell people that Facebook is trustworthy.</p>
