<p>Anytime you interact with a &quot;random&quot; non-friend (for example, a friend of a friend whose posted photo of your friend you comment on, or a wannabe friend whose friend invite you reply to with &quot;Sorry, you must have me confused with&#8230;&quot;), you are basically giving the &quot;random&quot; permission to view your profile **as if they were your friend** for 30 days!  A random non-friend whose note I had commented on started commenting on my photos. Creepy!</p>
