	<li id="comment-20592">
	<p>A useful setting for more serious privacy matters that didn&#039;t get mentioned is the &quot;Block List&quot;.  I didn&#039;t know about many of these security measures, this is a great post, but Block List works well to prevent specific people from finding you.  People can regularly send you messages even after you have unfriended them, but putting them on the Block List, in Privacy Settings, makes you unfindable for them on facebook- you do not exist.  You just type their name in a box.  Simpler than hiding from everyone, good for avoiding harassment.</p>
