	<li id="comment-21804">
	<p>ah, i found the answer about why we can&#039;t block google:</p>
<p>Unlike most sites on the Web, Facebook limits access to site information by third party search engine &quot;crawlers&quot; (e.g. Google, Yahoo, MSN, Ask). Facebook takes action to block access by these engines to personal information beyond your name, profile picture, and limited aggregated data about your profile (e.g. number of wall postings).</p>
<p>they won&#039;t allow them complete access to our information, but they will grant them access to our name, our friends, or whatever else you want displayed when someone finds you in a facebook search.</p>
	<p><cite>Comment by k. &#8212; March 1, 2009 @ <a href="#comment-21804">3:33 pm</a></cite> </p>
